1 AN ACT relating to the Public Service Student Loan Forgiveness Program, making
2 an appropriation therefor, and declaring an emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 164 IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) The General Assembly hereby establishes the Kentucky Public Service Student
7 Loan Forgiveness Program to encourage and assist individuals in pursuing or
8 remaining in public service professions.
9 (2) As used in this section:
10 (a) "Authority" means the Kentucky Higher Education Assistance Authority;
11 (b) "Eligible student loan" means a federally guaranteed student loan under
12 the Federal Family Education Loan Program or Federal Direct Loan
13 Program;
14 (c) "Public service" means employment with the Commonwealth of Kentucky,
15 any county, city, political subdivision, or department, board, agency,
16 commission or authority thereof, a public school district, public university,
17 or any qualifying nonprofit organization that is exempt from taxation under
18 26 U. S. C. sec. 501(c)(3) providing direct public services; and
19 (d) "Program agreement" means a contract entered into between the authority
20 and an eligible applicant for purposes of this section.
21 (3) (a) There is hereby established a Kentucky Public Service Student Loan
22 Forgiveness Program fund in the State Treasury for the purpose of
23 providing assistance in the repayment of eligible student loans to
24 individuals employed in a public service profession serving the citizens of
25 Kentucky.
26 (b) The fund shall be administered by the authority and shall consist of state
27 appropriations, gifts and grants from public and private sources, and
Page 1 of 4
