UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1979
1 federal funds.
2 (c) Any unallotted or unencumbered balances in the fund shall be invested as
3 provided in KRS 42.500. Income earned from the investments shall be
4 credited to the fund.
5 (d) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, any fund balance at the close of the fiscal
6 year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward to the next fiscal year.
7 (4) To be considered eligible for the program, an individual shall:
8 (a) Reside in the Commonwealth of Kentucky;
9 (b) Maintain full-time employment in a position of public service located in the
10 Commonwealth of Kentucky, excluding an office filled by election;
11 (c) Not be in default on any program under the Title IV of the Higher
12 Education Act of 1965, 20 U.S.C. sec. 1001 et seq., as amended, or any
13 obligation to the authority under any program administered by the
14 authority; and
15 (d) Submit an annual application that requires verification of public service
16 employment and the student loan.
17 (5) (a) Subject to the availability of funds, the authority shall award loan
18 repayment benefits to eligible applicants who are selected and who enter
19 into a program agreement. Recipients shall fulfill the requirements of the
20 agreement and comply with each of the following requirements while the
21 program agreement is in force:
22 1. Complete a minimum service commitment of two (2) years of full-time
23 eligible public service employment; and
24 2. Satisfy employment verification requirements.
25 (b) Failure to complete the service commitment may result in repayment
26 obligations or loss of remaining years of eligibility.
27 (6) (a) The authority shall administer the Kentucky Public Service Student Loan
Page 2 of 4
XXXX 3/3/2026 8:32 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1979
1 Forgiveness Program and develop award criteria to include but not be
2 limited to methods to address critical shortage occupations, rural or
3 distressed counties, underserved regions, length of service commitment, and
4 income thresholds.
5 (b) Subject to the availability of funds, the authority shall disburse loan
6 repayment benefits between five thousand dollars ($5,000) and seven
7 thousand five hundred dollars ($7,500) to a selected program participant
8 after the completion of each twelve (12) month period of verified public
9 service employment, not to exceed a period of five (5) consecutive years; and
10 (c) The lifetime loan repayment benefit disbursed to the program participant
11 shall not exceed a total of forty thousand dollars ($40,000), or the amount
12 of the outstanding eligible student loan balance, whichever is less.
13 (7) The authority may establish criteria for an enhanced award to include but not be
14 limited to:
15 (a) Loan repayment benefit up to ten thousand dollars ($10,000) to a program
16 participant after completion of each twelve (12) month period of eligible
17 public service employment not to exceed a period of five (5) consecutive
18 years;
19 (b) The total loan repayment benefit disbursed to an enhanced award program
20 participant not to exceed forty thousand dollars ($40,000), or the total loan
21 balances, whichever is less; and
22 (c) Develop selection criteria to address critical shortage of public service
23 professions, service to rural areas, designated distressed counties, health
24 professional shortage areas, and high-need school districts.
25 (8) The authority shall administer the Kentucky Public Service Student Loan
26 Forgiveness Program and shall promulgate administrative regulations in
27 accordance with KRS Chapter 13A for the administration of the program.
