UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1979
1 (9) (a) By November 1 of each year in which the Kentucky Public Service Student
2 Loan Forgiveness Program fund has a balance, the authority shall report to
3 the Legislative Research Commission for referral to the Interim Joint
4 Committee on Appropriations and Revenue:
5 1. The total number of eligible participants and loan repayment benefit
6 participants;
7 2. The total number and type of occupations participating in the
8 program;
9 3. The geographic distribution of loan repayment benefit recipients;
10 4. Retention rates; and
11 5. Total funds disbursed.
12 (b) The annual report shall provide an analysis and evaluation of the program
13 as it relates to workforce retention, regional equity, the cost per retained
14 public servant, and the return on investment relative to workforce vacancy
15 rates.
16 Section 2. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of
17 $30,000,000 in fiscal year 2026-2027 from the budget reserve trust fund account
18 established by KRS 48.705 to the Kentucky Public Service Student Loan Forgiveness
19 Program fund to provide assistance in the repayment of eligible student loans for public
20 service employees of the Commonwealth.
21 Section 3. There is hereby appropriated general fund moneys in the amount of
22 $30,000,000 in fiscal year 2027-2028 to the Kentucky Public Service Student Loan
23 Forgiveness Program fund to provide assistance in the repayment of eligible student loans
24 for public service employees of the Commonwealth.
25 Section 4. Whereas public service employees provide vital roles in the delivery
26 of critical and essential services in the Commonwealth, an emergency is declared to exist,
27 and this Act takes effect July 1, 2026.
